t" rep="norepeat">--act</arg><arg rep="repeat" choice="plain"> <replaceable>PATH</replaceable></arg><para/></cmdsynopsis></refsynopsisdiv><refsect><para>Main option:</para><variablelist spacing="compact"><varlistentry><term><option>--version</option></term><listitem><para>Show version.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term><option>--dry-run</option></term><listitem><para>Perform a trial run with no changes made.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term><option>--act</option></term><listitem><para>Depends on operation. May modify file.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term><option><replaceable>PATH</replaceable></option></term><listitem><para>The directory to search</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist><para>Directory traversal option:</para><variablelist spacing="compact"><varlistentry><term><option>--carryon</option></term><listitem><para>Process next file even if error occurs.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term><option>--maxdepth <replaceable>N</replaceable></option></term><listitem><para>Recurs directories only <option>N</option> level deep.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term><option>--mindepth <replaceable>N</replaceable></option></term><listitem><para>Process only files under <option>N</option> level deep.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term><option>-L</option></term><term><option>--follow</option></term><listitem><para>Follow symbolic links.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term><option>-d</option></term><term><option>--depth</option></term><listitem><para>Process each directory's contents before the directory itself.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term><option>-g <replaceable>GLOB</replaceable></option></term><listitem><para>File name glob. Example <quote>read*.txt</quote> for all text files whose filename starts with <quote>read</quote></para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term><option>-e <replaceable>PATTERN</replaceable></option></term><listitem><para>File name regular expression pattern. Example <quote>read.+\.txt</quote></para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist><para>Filter files:</para><variablelist spacing="compact"><varlistentry><term><option>--empty</option></term><listitem><para>Process only empty files or directories.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term><option>--no-empty</option></term><listitem><para>Process only non-empty files or directories.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term><option>--type <replaceable>CODE</replaceable></option></term><listitem><para>Filter the file type. See <xref linkend="filtertype"/> in manual.</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist><para>Operation option:</para><variablelist spacing="compact"><varlistentry><term><option>--del</option></term><listitem><para>Delete found files. Use <option>--act</option> to actually delete the file.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term><option>-s <replaceable>&lt;MATCH&gt;&lt;REPLACE&gt;</replaceable></option></term><term><option>--ren <replaceable>&lt;MATCH&gt;&lt;REPLACE&gt;</replaceable></option></term><listitem><para>Substitute file names to this regex pattern.
			This is similar to perl's substitution operator (s{}{}).
			The bracket quote ([], {}, &lt;&gt;, ()) must be balance.
			Use <option>--act</option> to rename the file.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term><option>--stat</option></term><listitem><para>Show statistics. The number of files, folders, total size.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term><option>--exstat</option></term><listitem><para>Show statistics about file extension. The number of files using a certain file extension.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term><option>-p <replaceable>MODULE</replaceable></option></term><term><option>--package <replaceable>MODULE</replaceable></option></term><listitem><para><option>MODULE</option> is module import name or the actual module file path to load.
			See <xref linkend="user-module"/> in manual.</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist><para>Pretty print options:</para><variablelist spacing="compact"><varlistentry><term><option>--basename</option></term><listitem><para>Print only name portion of path.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term><option>--mingw</option></term><listitem><para>Print path in MingW path format. For MS Windows only.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term><option>--cygwin</option></term><listitem><para>Print path in CygWin path format. For MS Windows only.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term><option>--uri</option></term><listitem><para>Print path in URI path format. e.g. <code>file:///B:/app/README</code></para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term><option>--rel-to <replaceable>DIR</replaceable></option></term><listitem><para>Print path relative to <option>DIR</option></para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist></refsect></refentry>
